>

1)install Git (if not installed)
After installation, check in terminal/command prompt:
>>>git --version

2)Initialize Git in your Eclipse project
Open Command Prompt / Terminal.

Navigate to your project folder:
>>>cd "C:\path\to\Stock-market-management"


3)Initialize Git:
>>>git init

3)Add all files
>>>git add .
The . means “add all files in this folder and subfolders.”

4️)Commit the files
git commit -m "Initial commit: Stock Market Management project"

5️)Connect to GitHub
Go to your GitHub repo → click Code → HTTPS → copy URL.
In terminal:
>>>git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/stock-market-mng.git

6️)Push to GitHub
git branch -M main
git push -u origin main
✅All files (Java, pom.xml, hibernate.cfg.xml, HTML/CSS/JS) will now appear on GitHub properly.

Tip: From now on, you just need to do:
git add .
git commit -m "Your message"
git push
